EncryptMessage.description: The EncryptMessage (General) function encrypts a message to provide privacy. EncryptMessage (General) allows an application to choose among cryptographic algorithms supported by the chosen mechanism. The EncryptMessage (General) function uses the security context referenced by the context handle. Some packages do not have messages to be encrypted or decrypted but rather provide an integrity hash that can be checked.

CertControlStore.description: The CertControlStore function allows an application to be notified when there is a difference between the contents of a cached store in use and the contents of that store as it is persisted to storage. Differences can occur as another process makes a change that affects the store as it is persisted.

CertOpenStore.description: The CertOpenStore function opens a certificate store by using a specified store provider type. While this function can open a certificate store for most purposes, CertOpenSystemStore is recommended to open the most common certificate stores. CertOpenStore is required for more complex options and special cases.

CryptAcquireContextA.description: The CryptAcquireContext function is used to acquire a handle to a particular key container within a particular cryptographic service provider (CSP). This returned handle is used in calls to CryptoAPI functions that use the selected CSP.

CryptAcquireContextW.description: The CryptAcquireContext function is used to acquire a handle to a particular key container within a particular cryptographic service provider (CSP). This returned handle is used in calls to CryptoAPI functions that use the selected CSP.

CryptCreateHash.description: The CryptCreateHash function initiates the hashing of a stream of data. It creates and returns to the calling application a handle to a cryptographic service provider (CSP) hash object. This handle is used in subsequent calls to CryptHashData and CryptHashSessionKey to hash session keys and other streams of data.

CryptDecodeObjectEx.description: The CryptDecodeObjectEx function decodes a structure of the type indicated by the lpszStructType parameter. CryptDecodeObjectEx offers a significant performance improvement over CryptDecodeObject by supporting memory allocation with the CRYPT_DECODE_ALLOC_FLAG value.

CryptDecrypt.description: The CryptDecrypt function decrypts data previously encrypted by using the CryptEncrypt function.

CryptEncrypt.description: The CryptEncrypt function encrypts data. The algorithm used to encrypt the data is designated by the key held by the CSP module and is referenced by the hKey parameter.

CryptGenKey.description: The CryptGenKey function generates a random cryptographic session key or a public/private key pair. A handle to the key or key pair is returned in phKey. This handle can then be used as needed with any CryptoAPI function that requires a key handle.

CryptHashData.description: The CryptHashData function adds data to a specified hash object. This function and CryptHashSessionKey can be called multiple times to compute the hash of long or discontinuous data streams.

IWbemServices_ExecQuery.description: The CryptExportKey function exports a cryptographic key or a key pair from a cryptographic service provider (CSP) in a secure manner.

MessageBoxTimeoutW.description: The CryptEncrypt function encrypts data. The algorithm used to encrypt the data is designated by the key held by the CSP module and is referenced by the hKey parameter.
